%vlocity_namespace%__PropertySet__c.label: Please Read Regarding Type of HRA Choices
%vlocity_namespace%__PropertySet__c.text:
Member Pay HRA

Member is provided a debit card and decides how and when to use their HRA dollars to pay for covered expenses.  The medical and Rx would both be member pay via a debit card.  A Member Pay HRA can also be cardless, which means that no debit card is issued and the member decides how and when to use their HRA dollars by reimbursing themselves or initiating payments to providers on the web portal or mobile app.

Provider Pay HRA

This is the only HRA plan that allows for an upfront deductible plan type and the only HRA plan that allows for medical split % plans.  The medical and Rx would both auto-pay the provider if there are dollars available in the HRA account at the time the claim is received.

 Provider Pay HRA with Optional Rx/Dental/Vision Debit Card

Select this plan if the employer offers Dental and/or Vision as a service reimbursable out of the HRA, they will always be carded/member pay.  Select this plan if the employer requires that the Medical is provider pay and the Rx is carded/member pay.
